<div class=3D"box" id=3D"help">
<label>Help</label>
<p>
Press <kbd>Alt</kbd> with the appropriate letter. For example, to type <spa=
n class=3D"char">=C9=94</span> or <span class=3D"char">=C9=92</span>, hold =
<kbd>Alt</kbd> and press <kbd>O</kbd> once or twice.
</p><p>
Stop the mouse over each button to learn its keyboard shortcut.
</p><p><span class=3D"if-clipboard-writing"><kbd>Alt=E2=80=8A+=E2=80=8Aclic=
k</kbd> a button to copy a single character to the clipboard.</span></p><p>=
You can select text and press <kbd class=3D"clipboard">Ctrl=E2=80=8A+=E2=80=
=8AC</kbd> to copy it to your docu=C2=ADment. In your target document, pres=
s <kbd class=3D"clipboard">Ctrl=E2=80=8A+=E2=80=8AV</kbd>, or, if you want =
to paste the text without formatting, try <kbd class=3D"clipboard">Ctrl=E2=
=80=8A+=E2=80=8AShift=E2=80=8A+=E2=80=8AV</kbd>.</p>=09
<p>
